Mkhize in a tweet that 5G is a technology issue and COVID-19 is a virus and people cannot link the virus to technology. Claims that 5G technology could be linked to the spread of the coronavirus have been spreading online for weeks. An American medical doctor Thomas Cowan speaking in Tuscon, Arizona in March 2019 also advanced the conspiracy theory, in a video that has been viewed thousands of times on YouTube. But to date, there has been no scientific connection between the spread of the virus and the 5G technology. The South African Health Minister said people need to use facts to fight coronavirus. “We have tracked the virus from animals to human beings. Let’s tell the truth. We can prevent the spread.” --BBC--